The traffic split occurs just before the Bronx anchorage before traffic lanes converge again just after the Queens anchorage prior to the Cross Island Parkway exit ramp While there will be no loss of traffic lane capacity once the new pattern is established crews will continue using a moveable barrier that can be shifted to allow for three Bronx-bound lanes in the morning (5 a.m. to 10 a.m.) and three Queens-bound lanes in the afternoon (2 p.m. to 10 p.m.) on weekdays. Through Summer 2021
